SIMPLE: twire
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twire
<hw>Twire</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>tweern</ets>, G. <ets>zwirn</ets>, and E. <ets>twine</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A twisted filament; a thread.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twire
<hw>Twire</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. MHG. <ets>zwieren</ets>, E.
<ets>thwart</ets>, and <ets>queer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
peep; to glance obliquely; to leer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which maids will <qex>twire</qex> at 'tween their fingers.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I saw the wench that <qex>twired</qex> and twinkled at thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To twinkle; to glance; to gleam.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When sparkling stars <qex>twire</qex> not.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twire</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twire
<hw>Twire</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To sing, or twitter.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twire-pipe</ent>⟦br⟧
